These are the external modules brought in for this application.
 The main modules used are xlsx, fs, j2xls, and underscore
 xlsx is an excel parser
 fs is used with j2xls to write the output
 underscore is used for sorting and managing lists/objects

classitems.name: assign

params.name: roomnum
params.description: The room to have the group-class added to it

params.name: classinfo
params.description: The class to be added to the room

classitems.description:
Takes an approved room number and group-class
and puts them in the schedule for the proper days.
This is used for adding other group-classes as data
to see if the room is open at this time.

classitems.name: findroom

params.name: classinfo
params.description: The class to find the room for

classitems.description:
findroom takes all the rooms available and sorts them by capacity
then it finds the smallest room available for the class in question.
There is no return, but it does generate a list of acceptable classrooms: that is classrooms that can hold this class.

classitems.name: checkAvailable
classitems.description:
Checks if the room is available for all days and times that the class has a session.
Returns true for available and false for not available.

classitems.name: checkTime

params.name: starttime
params.description: start time of the class to check the room for availability

params.name: roominfo
params.description: day array of the room in question

return.description: True for open or False for closed/taken

classitems.description: Checks the specific time of the day array to see if it is open.

classitems.name: getvalue

params.name: oldtime
params.description: Time in the format of 10:00:00 AM

classitems.description: Takes time stamp and converts it to a single number for comparisons.
